{{Nihongo|'''Daichi Kamada'''|鎌田 大地|Kamada Daichi|born 5 August 1996}} is a Japanese professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[central midfielder]] or [[attacking midfielder]] for {{English football updater|CrystalP}} club [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] and the [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]].

After representing several Japanese football academies including school football, Kamada began his career at [[Sagan Tosu]] in early 2015, where he spent two and a half years. In the second half of 2017, he moved abroad to German club [[Eintracht Frankfurt]]. During his six years at the club, Kamada won the [[DFB-Pokal]] in the [[2017–18 DFB-Pokal|2017–18 season]] and the [[UEFA Europa League]] in [[2021–22 UEFA Europa League|2021–22]], while he was loaned to Belgian club Sint-Truiden in the 2018–19 season.

In the second half of 2023, Kamada left Frankfurt to join Italian club [[SS Lazio|Lazio]] on a two-year contract, however he departed the club a year early. In July 2024, Kamada joined Premier League side Crystal Palace, and he helped the club win the [[FA Cup]] in his [[2025 FA Cup final|first season]].

A former Japan youth international, Kamada made his senior debut in 2019, and was part of his country's squad at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Born in [[Ehime]], Japan, Kamada began playing football at "Kids FC" (now FC Zebra Kids) and helped the side win TV Ehime Cup Ehime Prefectural Youth Soccer Championship U-12 when he was in 6th grade of elementary school.<ref name="Kamada Interview 1">{{cite news |date=10 March 2017 |title=【The Real】成長途上の20歳・鎌田大地が秘めた可能性…サガン鳥栖の至宝から日本代表の司令塔へ |trans-title=[The Real] The potential of 20-year-old Daichi Kamada in his development... From the gem of Sagan Tosu to the playmaker of the Japan national team. |url=https://cyclestyle.net/article/2017/03/10/46258.html |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Cycle Style |language=ja}}</ref> When Kamada was in junior high school, he then joined [[Gamba Osaka]] and was selected for the U-13 J League.<ref name="Kamada Interview 1"/> However, due to injuries, Kamada was released from the club and he returned to play school football, joining Higashiyama High School in 2012.<ref name="Kamada Interview 1"/><ref>{{cite news |date=28 July 2012 |title=[総体]出場校紹介:東山(京都) |trans-title=[National High School Championship] Participating School Introduction: Higashiyama (Kyoto). |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?102682-104416-fl |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=12 October 2019 |title=帽子にイヤホンつけ…「なんじゃこいつ」 恩師が明かす、鎌田大地の"変貌"秘話 |trans-title=Wearing a hat with earphones... "What is this guy?" His former coach reveals the secret behind Daichi Kamada's "transformation." |url=https://www.football-zone.net/archives/222775 |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Football Zone |language=ja}}</ref> Kamada quickly made an impact at Higashiyama, playing as an attacking midfielder.<ref name="Kamada Interview 2"/><ref>{{cite news |date=11 May 2013 |title=[JFAプレミアカップ]2年ぶりV目指すG大阪ジュニアユースが怒涛の9発勝利 |trans-title=[JFA Premier Cup] Gamba Osaka Junior Youth, aiming for their first victory in two years, achieves a stunning 9-goal victory. |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?83886-77776-fl |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}<br />{{cite news |date=8 May 2013 |title=[プリンスリーグ関西1部]小屋松2発の京都橘と野洲撃破の大阪桐蔭が開幕5連勝:第5節 |trans-title=[Prince League Kansai Division 1] Kyoto Tachibana with two goals from Koyamatsu and Osaka Toin with a victory over Yasu both achieve their fifth consecutive win in the opening matches: Round 5. |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?114383-116554-fl |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}<br />{{cite news |date=3 June 2013 |title=[MOM781]東山MF鎌田大地(2年)_主将不在のチームを支える2年生エース |trans-title=[MOM781] Higashiyama MF Daichi Kamada (2nd year) _ The second-year ace who supports the team in the absence of the captain. |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?115519-119718-fl |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}<br />{{cite news |date=1 July 2013 |title=[プリンスリーグ関西1部]第7節試合結果 |trans-title=[Prince League Kansai Division 1] Round 7 match results. |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?116658-116557-fl |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}<br />{{cite news |date=7 July 2013 |title=[プリンスリーグ関西1部]第8節試合結果 |trans-title=[Prince League Kansai Division 1] Round 8 match results. |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?116944-116558-fl |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}</ref> He went on to make 18 appearances and scored 22 at the end of the 2013 season.<ref name="Kamada Interview 2"/><ref>{{cite news |date=21 July 2013 |title=[プリンスリーグ関西1部]第11節試合結果 |trans-title=[Prince League Kansai Division 1] Round 11 match results. |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?117630-116561-fl |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}<br />{{cite news |date=7 September 2013 |title=[プリンスリーグ関西1部]第14節試合結果 |trans-title=[Prince League Kansai Division 1] Round 14 match results. |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?120342-116564-fl |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}<br />{{cite news |date=28 September 2013 |title=[プリンスリーグ関西1部]第16節試合結果 |trans-title=[Prince League Kansai Division 1] Round 16 match results. |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?121369-116567-fl |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}<br />{{cite news |date=6 October 2013 |title=[プリンスリーグ関西1部]5発快勝!大阪桐蔭が関西1部制す!!:第18節 |trans-title=[Prince League Kansai Division 1] 5–0 dominant win! Osaka Toin clinches the Kansai Division 1 title!!: Round 18. |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?121874-116569-fl |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}<br />{{cite news |date=16 December 2013 |title=[MOM911]東山高FW鎌田大地(2年)_新チーム初陣で見せた中心選手にふさわしい働き |trans-title=[MOM911] Higashiyama High FW Daichi Kamada (2nd year) _ A performance worthy of a key player in the team's first match of the new season. |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?125455-129886-fl |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}</ref>

In his third year at Higashiyama High School, Kamada was appointed captain, but they finished at the bottom of the league table with 2 wins and 13 losses.<ref name="Kamada Interview 2"/><ref>{{cite news|title=中西が頭で2発!立命館宇治が逆転V:京都新人戦|url=http://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?133616-133616-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=25 February 2014|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=[MOM1006]東山MF井村泰誓(3年)_プロ注目の"潤滑油"|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?136320-136320-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=9 April 2014|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=帽子にイヤホンつけ…「なんじゃこいつ」 恩師が明かす、鎌田大地の"変貌"秘話"|url=https://www.football-zone.net/archives/222775/2|publisher=Football Zone|language=ja|date=12 October 2019|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title= [プレミアリーグWEST]進路注目の東山FW鎌田「全国行ったら絶対にやれると思う」|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?148339-148339-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=29 September 2014|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=[プレミアリーグWEST]G大阪ユースFW中村が劇的Vヘッド!首位・名古屋U18が初黒星:第8節|url=http://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?135865-135865-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=14 July 2014|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> Despite this, he continued to impress, having scored ten goals, making him the fourth top scorer in the 2014 season.<ref name="Kamada Interview 2"/><ref>{{cite news|title=[プレミアリーグWEST]昇格組同士の京都ダービー、注目FW鎌田V弾で東山が京都橘撃破!|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?136319-136319-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=7 April 2014|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=[プレミアリーグWEST]プロ注目の"2枚看板"不在も東福岡が東山に5発快勝|url=http://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?148318-148318-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=29 September 2014|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=[選手権予選]ユース取材ライター陣が推薦する「選手権予選注目の11傑」vol.1|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?149804-149804-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=20 October 2014|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=[選手権予選]ユース取材ライター陣が推薦する「選手権予選注目の11傑」vol.3|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?149931-149931-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=22 October 2014|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title= [プレミアリーグWEST]得点ランキング|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?142773-142773-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=6 December 2014|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref><ref name="Kamada Higashiyama High School">{{cite news |date=19 May 2015 |title=[総体]鳥栖でブレイク中の鎌田擁した昨年以上のまとまりと伸びシロ、東山は成長遂げて京都突破へ |trans-title=[National High School Championship] Higashiyama, with the improved cohesion and potential surpassing last year, featuring the rising Kamada from Tosu, aims to break through to Kyoto. |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?163346-163346-fl |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}</ref> At the end of the 2014 season, Kamada's performance at Higashiyama High School having impressed many, he supposedly attracted interest from at least five [[J. League]] clubs following his graduation.<ref name="Kamada Interview 3"/><ref>{{cite news|title= [高卒]Jクラブ15年加入内定者一覧(12/24)|url=http://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?150476-150476-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=1 September 2014|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> On 17 November 2014, Kamada was announced as a new signing for [[Sagan Tosu]] for the 2015 season.<ref>{{cite news|title=サガン鳥栖、東山高DF鎌田大地の来季加入内定を発表|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/jl/20141117/251078.html|publisher=Soccer King|language=ja|date=17 November 2014|access-date=31 August 2024}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.saga-s.co.jp/articles/-/58526|title=１８歳ＭＦ鎌田加入 京都・東山高|publisher=Sagan Tosu|language=ja|date=17 November 2014|access-date=19 July 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200718154036/https://www.saga-s.co.jp/articles/-/58526|archive-date=18 July 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Ahead of the 2015 season, he was given the number 24 shirt.<ref>{{cite news|title=鳥栖が2015シーズンの背番号を発表…新加入ペク・ソンドンは「9」に|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/jl/20150119/272926.html|website=Soccer King|language=ja|date=19 January 2015|access-date=31 August 2024}}</ref>

===Sagan Tosu===
At the start of the 2015 season, Kamada was loaned out to [[J.League U-22 Selection|J.League U-22]], where he made two appearances for the side.<ref>{{cite web |date=20 March 2015 |title=Jリーグ・アンダー22選抜に鎌田大地選手選出のお知らせ |trans-title=Announcement: Daichi Kamada selected for the J.League Under-22 selection. |url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/news/p/210/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200718160610/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/news/p/210/ |archive-date=18 July 2020 |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Sagan Tosu |language=ja}}<br />{{cite news |date=21 March 2015 |title=山口vsJ-22 試合記録 |trans-title=Yamaguchi vs J-22 Match Record. |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?159246-159246-fl |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}<br />{{cite web |date=12 June 2015 |title=Jリーグ・アンダー22選抜に鎌田大地選手選出のお知らせ |trans-title=Announcement: Daichi Kamada selected for the J.League Under-22 selection. |url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/news/p/443/ |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200812231132/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/news/p/443/ |archive-date=12 August 2020 |access-date=7 September 2024 |website=Sagan Tosu |language=ja}}</ref> He made his Sagan Tosu debut, coming on as a 75th-minute substitute, in a 1–0 loss against [[Albirex Niigata]] in the J.League Cup on 8 April.<ref>{{cite web |date=8 April 2015 |title=アルビレックス新潟 vs サガン鳥栖 |trans-title=Albirex Niigata vs Sagan Tosu. |url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2015040803/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200718161314/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2015040803/ |archive-date=18 July 2020 |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Sagan Tosu |language=ja}}</ref> A month later on 10 May, Kamada scored his first goal on his J.League debut, having come on as a 72nd-minute substitute, in a 1–1 draw against [[Matsumoto Yamaga FC|Matsumoto Yamaga]].<ref>{{cite news |date=10 May 2015 |title=鳥栖、リーグ戦デビューの高卒ルーキー鎌田が起死回生の同点弾 |trans-title=Tosu's high school graduate rookie Kamada scores a game-tying goal in his league debut, saving the team. |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?162773-162773-fl |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}</ref> This was followed up by setting up the winning goal for [[Yohei Toyoda]] to help Sagan Tosu win 1–0.<ref>{{cite news |date=16 May 2015 |title=名古屋vs鳥栖 試合記録 |trans-title=Nagoya vs Tosu Match Record. |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?163160-163160-fl |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}</ref> His first five appearances of the season earned him awarded New Hero Awards of the Yamazaki Nabisco Cup.<ref>{{cite news |date=18 May 2015 |title=ヤマザキナビスコ杯「ニューヒーロー賞」の第2回投票途中結果発表 |trans-title=Yamazaki Nabisco Cup "New Hero Award" Second Round Voting Interim Results Announcement. |url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/ync/20150518/313669.html |access-date=7 September 2024 |website=Soccer King |language=ja}}</ref> He then set up two goals, in a 3–2 win against [[Kashiwa Reysol]] on 11 July.<ref>{{cite news |date=11 July 2015 |title=鎌田が圧巻2A!鳥栖が柏の反撃を振り切り6試合ぶり勝利 |trans-title=Kamada delivers an impressive 2 assists! Tosu shakes off Kashiwa's comeback to secure a victory for the first time in 6 matches. |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?166966-166966-fl |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}</ref> Eleven days later on 22 July 2015, Kamada scored his second goal of the season, in a 1–1 draw against Gamba Osaka.<ref>{{cite web |date=22 July 2015 |title=ガンバ大阪 1–1 サガン鳥栖 |trans-title=Gamba Osaka 1–1 Sagan Tosu. |url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2015072213/ |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20240901142724/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2015072213/ |archive-date=1 September 2024 |access-date=7 September 2024 |website=Sagan Tosu |language=ja}}</ref> Having started out on the substitute bench, Kamada became a first team regular for the side, playing in the midfield position.<ref name="Kamada Interview 4">{{cite news |date=22 April 2020 |title=鎌田大地は「やっぱり掴めない」。東山高時代の覚醒と葛藤、そして今 (4) |trans-title=Daichi Kamada: "I still can't grasp it." The awakening and struggles from his days at Higashiyama High School, and where he is now (4). |url=https://number.bunshun.jp/articles/-/843267?page=4 |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Number Bunshun |language=ja}}</ref><ref name="Kamada Higashiyama High School"/><ref>{{cite news |date=12 July 2015 |title=2アシストで鳥栖を勝利に導いたFW鎌田、代表も視野に「結果を出し続けたい」 |trans-title=With two assists, FW Kamada led Tosu to victory and aims for the national team, saying, "I want to keep delivering results." |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?166998-166998-fl |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Web Gekisaka |language=ja}}<br />{{cite news |date=25 December 2015 |title=鳥栖、「豊田依存」から抜け出せずホーム戦わずか4勝。マガト氏招聘も不透明に【2015年通信簿】 |trans-title=Tosu fails to break free from "reliance on Toyota," with only four home wins. The hiring of Magath is also uncertain. [2015 Report Card] |url=https://www.footballchannel.jp/2015/12/25/post128940/ |access-date=7 September 2024 |website=Football Channel |language=ja}}</ref> Despite suffering an injury later in the 2015 season, he went on make twenty–eight appearances and score three times in all competitions.<ref>{{cite web |date=16 August 2015 |title=モンテディオ山形 1–3 サガン鳥栖 |trans-title=Montedio Yamagata 1–3 Sagan Tosu. |url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2015081615/ |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20240901122655/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2015081615/ |archive-date=1 September 2024 |access-date=7 September 2024 |website=Sagan Tosu |language=ja}}<br />{{cite web |date=21 September 2015 |title=Jリーグ・アンダー22選抜に鎌田大地選手選出のお知ら |trans-title=Announcement: Daichi Kamada selected for the J.League Under-22 selection. |url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/news/p/685/ |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200718184352/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/news/p/685/ |archive-date=18 July 2020 |access-date=7 September 2024 |website=Sagan Tosu |language=ja}}<br />{{cite web |date=22 September 2015 |title=鎌田大地選手、Jリーグ・アンダー22選抜辞退のお知らせ |trans-title=Announcement: Daichi Kamada withdraws from the J.League Under-22 selection. |url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/news/p/687/ |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171025044321/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/news/p/687/ |archive-date=25 October 2017 |access-date=7 September 2024 |website=Sagan Tosu |language=ja}}</ref>

Ahead of the 2016 season, Kamada signed a contract with the club.<ref>{{cite web |date=16 January 2016 |title=鎌田大地選手 契約更新のお知らせ |trans-title=Announcement: Daichi Kamada contract renewal. |url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/news/p/941/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200718184854/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/news/p/941/ |archive-date=18 July 2020 |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Sagan Tosu |language=ja}}</ref> At the start of the season, he started in midfield for the first seven matches.<ref>{{cite news|title=金崎、決勝ヘッド!!鹿島が2戦連続1–0勝利で開幕2連勝|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?184325-184325-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=6 March 2016|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=苦悩する鳥栖MF鎌田は俊輔から刺激「あれくらい自分も…」|url=http://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?185414-185414-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=19 March 2016|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=最も走ったチーム&選手は…J1第1S第5節の走行距離発表|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?186573-186573-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=4 April 2016|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> Kamada contributed two assists in two matches between 2 and 6 April against Kashiwa Reysol and [[Vegalta Sendai]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2016040203/|title=4/2 (土) 明治安田Ｊ１リーグ 第5節 サガン鳥栖 v 柏レイソル|website=Sagan Tosu|language=ja|date=2 April 2016|access-date=7 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20240901111842/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2016040203/|archive-date=1 September 2024|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2016040606/|title=サガン鳥栖 1–1 ベガルタ仙台|website=Sagan Tosu|language=ja|date=6 April 2016|access-date=7 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20240901145258/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2016040606/|archive-date=1 September 2024|url-status=live}}</ref> For his performance, he, once again, awarded New Hero Awards of the Yamazaki Nabisco Cup.<ref>{{cite news|title=「ニューヒーロー賞」グループステージ第3節終了時点の得票上位選手を発表【ヤマザキナビスコカップ】|url=http://www.jleague.jp/news/article/5593/|website=J. League Official Website|language=ja|date=18 April 2016|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=横浜FMのFW富樫敬真や鳥栖のMF鎌田大地らが引き続き選出…「ニューヒーロー賞」第2回途中集計結果発表《ナビスコカップ》|url=https://web.ultra-soccer.jp/news/view?news_no=240529|website=Web Ultra Soccer|language=ja|date=16 May 2016|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> However, during a match against [[Yokohama F. Marinos]] on 20 April, he suffered an elbow injury and was substituted as a result.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2016042007/|title=横浜Ｆ・マリノス vs サガン鳥栖|publisher=Sagan Tosu|language=ja|date=20 April 2016|access-date=19 July 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200718195051/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2016042007/|archive-date=18 July 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Following this, it was announced on 22 April that Kamada was out for two weeks.<ref>{{cite web |date=22 April 2016 |title=鎌田大地選手 負傷のお知らせ |trans-title=Announcement: Daichi Kamada injury. |url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/news/p/1175/ |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210510020037/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/news/p/1175/ |archive-date=10 May 2021 |access-date=7 September 2024 |website=Sagan Tosu |language=ja}}</ref> It wasn't until 13 May when he returned to the starting line–up against [[FC Tokyo]] and played 55 minutes before being substituted, in a 0–0 draw.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2016051301/|title=ＦＣ東京 0–0 サガン鳥栖|website=Sagan Tosu|language=ja|date=13 May 2016|access-date=7 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20240901115224/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2016051301/|archive-date=1 September 2024|url-status=live}}</ref> On 18 June, Kamada scored his first goals of the season, in a 2–1 win against Gamba Osaka.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2016061809/|title=サガン鳥栖 2–1 ガンバ大阪|website=Sagan Tosu|language=ja|date=18 June 2016|access-date=7 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20240901115134/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2016061809/|archive-date=1 September 2024|url-status=live}}</ref> Since returning to the first team from injury, he regained his first team place for the rest of the season.<ref name="Kamada Interview 4"/><ref>{{cite news|title=僕らがサッカーボーイズだった頃3 日本代表への道|url=https://www.footballchannel.jp/2016/06/24/post160044/|website=Football Channel|language=ja|date=24 June 2016|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=エース豊田2発! 鳥栖が敵地で湘南を圧倒し3戦無敗|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?193936-193936-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=13 July 2016|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=ハリルJに推薦したいJリーガー。期待の新戦力候補たち。2016年10月シリーズ編【編集部フォーカス】|url=http://www.footballchannel.jp/2016/09/28/post177121/|website=Football Channel|language=ja|date=28 September 2016|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=ハリルJに推薦したい5人。期待の新戦力候補たち。2016年11月シリーズ編【編集部フォーカス】|url=http://www.footballchannel.jp/2016/11/02/post182759/3/|website=Football Channel|language=ja|date=2 November 2016|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> Kamada then scored five more goals later in the season, including scoring twice in a 3–2 win against Kashiwa Reysol on 22 October.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2016070908/|title=ヴィッセル神戸 vs サガン鳥栖|website=Sagan Tosu|language=ja|date=9 July 2016|access-date=7 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419064222/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2016070908/|archive-date=19 April 2020|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2016072309/|title=アビスパ福岡 vs サガン鳥栖|website=Sagan Tosu|language=ja|date=23 July 2016|access-date=7 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20211128143224/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2016072309/|archive-date=28 November 2021|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2016082007/|title=ジュビロ磐田 1–1 サガン鳥栖|website=Sagan Tosu|language=ja|date=20 August 2016|access-date=7 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20240901120057/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2016082007/|archive-date=1 September 2024|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/836/|title=サガン鳥栖 3–0ＦＣ琉球|website=Sagan Tosu|language=ja|date=1 September 2016|access-date=7 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20240901120054/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/836/|archive-date=1 September 2024|url-status=live}}</ref> His goal against Kashiwa Reysol earned him J League Goal of the Month.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/news/p/1682/|title=鎌田大地選手 2016 明治安田生命Ｊ１リーグ・10月月間ベストゴール選出のお知らせ|website=Sagan Tosu|language=ja|date=10 November 2016|access-date=7 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200718205015/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/news/p/1682/|archive-date=18 July 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> By the end of the season, he made thirty–four appearances and scoring eight times in all competitions.

Ahead of the 2017 season, Kamada switched number shirt from twenty–four to seven.<ref>{{cite news|title=鳥栖が今季の背番号発表…鎌田大地が「7」、新加入の小林祐三は「13」に|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/jl/20170114/541511.html|publisher=Soccer King|language=ja|date=14 January 2017|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> He also signed a contract extension with Sagan Tosu.<ref>{{cite web |date=13 January 2017 |title=鎌田大地選手 契約更新のお知らせ |trans-title=Announcement: Daichi Kamada contract renewal. |url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/news/p/1817/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200718205016/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/news/p/1817/ |archive-date=18 July 2020 |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Sagan Tosu |language=ja}}</ref> At the start of the season, Kamada continued to regain his first team place, playing in the midfield position.<ref name="Kamada Interview 4"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2017031103/|title=サガン鳥栖 vs サンフレッチェ広島|website=Sagan Tosu|language=ja|date=11 March 2017|access-date=7 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171225145222/http://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2017031103/|archive-date=25 December 2017|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite news|title=最も走ったチーム&選手は…J1第6節の走行距離発表|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?213423-213423-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=10 April 2017|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=最も走ったチーム&選手は…J1第10節の走行距離発表|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?215709-215709-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=8 May 2017|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> He scored three times in April, including a brace in a 4–4 draw against [[Cerezo Osaka]] in the J.League Cup on 26 April <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2017040106/|title=ＦＣ東京 vs サガン鳥栖|website=Sagan Tosu|language=ja|date=1 April 2017|access-date=7 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171225141826/http://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2017040106/|archive-date=25 December 2017|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|url=http://sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2017042608/|title=サガン鳥栖 vs セレッソ大阪|website=Sagan Tosu|language=ja|date=26 April 2017|access-date=7 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170823012611/http://sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2017042608/|archive-date=23 August 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> The following month saw Kamada score two more goals for the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2017050703/|title=サガン鳥栖 vs 横浜Ｆ・マリノス|website=Sagan Tosu|language=ja|date=7 May 2017|access-date=7 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170823050639/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2017050703/|archive-date=23 August 2017|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2017052706/|title=サガン鳥栖 vs 北海道コンサドーレ札幌|website=Sagan Tosu|language=ja|date=27 May 2017|access-date=7 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170823045606/http://sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2017052706/|archive-date=23 August 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> He made his last appearance of the season against [[Urawa Red Diamonds]] on 25 June, setting up the club's first goal of the game in a 2–1 win.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2017062509/|title=サガン鳥栖 2–1 浦和レッズ|website=Sagan Tosu|language=ja|date=25 June 2017|access-date=7 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20240901140034/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/match/schedule/2017062509/|archive-date=1 September 2024|url-status=live}}</ref> In his final season, Kamada made 16 appearances, scoring three goals.<ref name="frankfurt"/>

===Eintracht Frankfurt===
In June 2017, Kamada joined [[Bundesliga]] club [[Eintracht Frankfurt]], signing a four-year contract running until 2021.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eintracht.de/news/artikel/daichi-kamada-erhaelt-vierjahres-vertrag-am-main-60669/|title=Daichi Kamada erhält Vierjahres-Vertrag am Main|publisher=Eintracht Frankfurt|language=de|date=29 June 2017|access-date=19 July 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170629185914/https://www.eintracht.de/news/artikel/daichi-kamada-erhaelt-vierjahres-vertrag-am-main-60669/|archive-date=29 June 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> The transfer fee was reported as €2.5 million.<ref name="frankfurt">{{cite news |date=29 June 2017 |title=Offiziell: Kamada verstärkt Eintracht Frankfurt |trans-title=Official: Kamada strengthens Eintracht Frankfurt. |url=https://www.kicker.de/offiziell_kamada-verstaerkt-eintracht-frankfurt-700599/artikel |access-date=29 June 2017 |work=kicker Online |language=de}}<br />{{cite web |date=24 June 2017 |title=鎌田大地選手 アイントラハト・フランクフルトへ完全移籍のお知らせ |trans-title=Announcement: Daichi Kamada completes permanent transfer to Eintracht Frankfurt. |url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/news/p/2211/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200718205007/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/news/p/2211/ |archive-date=18 July 2020 |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Sagan Tosu |language=ja}}</ref>

Kamada made his Eintracht Frankfurt debut in the first round of the DFB–Pokal, starting a match and played 73 minutes before being substituted, in a 3–0 win against [[TuS Erndtebrück]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Frankfurt lässt in Unterzahl nichts anbrennen|url=https://www.kicker.de/tus-erndtebrueck-gegen-frankfurt-2017-dfb-pokal-3815575/analyse|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=12 August 2017|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> In a follow–up match against [[SC Freiburg]], he made his league debut for the club, starting a match and played 67 minutes before being substituted, in a 0–0 draw.<ref>{{cite news|title=Videobeweis rettet Frankfurt, die Latte Freiburg|url=https://www.kicker.de/freiburg-gegen-frankfurt-2017-bundesliga-3827249/analyse|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=20 August 2017|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> However, Kamada found his first team opportunities at Eintracht Frankfurt, due to competitions and his own injury concern.<ref name="Kamada Interview 5">{{cite news|title=鎌田大地は「やっぱり掴めない」。東山高時代の覚醒と葛藤、そして今 (5)|url=https://number.bunshun.jp/articles/-/843267?page=5|publisher=Number Bunshun|language=ja|date=22 April 2020|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Mit bewährter Taktik nach Köln|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/bewaehrter-taktik-nach-koeln-11021510.html|publisher=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=19 September 2017|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Wechselt noch ein Härtefall? |url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/wechselt-noch-haertefall-10987735.html|publisher=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=25 January 2018|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Höhere Dichte in Breite und Spitze|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/hoehere-dichte-breite-spitze-11016174.html|publisher=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=12 February 2018|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Zwischenzeugnis: Note 2|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/zwischenzeugnis-note-11002009.html|publisher=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=22 December 2017|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Frisch in den Norden|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/frisch-norden-11001966.html|publisher=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=12 December 2017|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> Manager [[Niko Kovač]] said about his progress, saying: "Another reason for Daichi was that he is extraordinarily good in terms of ball technique and that he is very good in the gaps, which the opponent cannot really control moves. Unfortunately he got off a little bit badly because he was pushed away from time to time. You have to give him the time, he'll get that too."<ref>{{cite news|title=Warum Kamada statt Hrgota stürmte|url=https://www.kicker.de/warum-kamada-statt-hrgota-stuermte-704506/artikel|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=22 August 2017|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> At the end of the 2017–18 season, he made four appearances in all competitions.

====Sint-Truiden (loan)====
In order to receive first team football, Kamada was loaned out to Belgian side [[Sint-Truidense V.V.|Sint-Truiden]] for the rest of the 2018–19 season on 1 September 2018.<ref>{{cite news |date=1 September 2018 |title=Frankfurt leiht Japaner Kamada an belgischen Club aus |trans-title=Frankfurt loans Japanese player Kamada to a Belgian club. |url=https://www.fr.de/sport/fussball/frankfurt-leiht-japaner-kamada-belgischen-club-10971635.html |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Frankfurter Rundschau |language=de}}<br />{{cite news |date=29 June 2018 |title=Auf dem Eintracht-Karussell |url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-karussell-10982747.html |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Frankfurter Rundschau |language=de}}</ref> Kamada quickly made an impact for the club when he scored on his debut, in a 2–1 win against [[K.A.A. Gent|Gent]] on 16 September 2018.<ref>{{cite news|title=Briljante dribbel van Japanse invaller bezorgt KAA Gent een ijskoude douche|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/live/voetbal/280037|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|language=nl|date=16 September 2018|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> This was followed up by scoring in a 2–0 win against [[Royal Antwerp F.C.|Royal Antwerp]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stvv.com/nl/nieuws/a-kern/wedstrijdverslag-stvv-vs-antwerp-v1|title=STVV KLOPT RAFC MET 2–0!|publisher=Sint-Truidense V.V.|language=nl|date=22 September 2018|access-date=19 July 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419123947/https://www.stvv.com/nl/nieuws/a-kern/wedstrijdverslag-stvv-vs-antwerp-v1|archive-date=19 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Since making his debut for Sint-Truiden, Kamada quickly established himself in the first team, playing in either midfielder and striker positions.<ref name="Kamada Interview 5" /><ref>{{cite news|title=Japanse spits van STVV is dé revelatie van de Jupiler Pro League: acht goals uit amper zes basisplaatsen|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20181110_03933558|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|language=nl|date=10 November 2018|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Vijf zaken die u moet weten over de goalgetter van STVV, de rijzende ster in onze competitie|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20181114_03943794|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|language=nl|date=14 November 2018|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=ベルギーで得点量産の鎌田大地、復活の2018年に「よくここまで自分の状態を戻せた」|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?262648-262648-f|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=27 December 2018|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Kamada aan de aftrap?|url=https://www.hbvl.be/cnt/dmf20181004_03809994/kamada-aan-de-aftrap|publisher=HBVL|language=nl|date=4 October 2018|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title="Elke spits kent periode van twijfels"|url=https://www.hbvl.be/cnt/dmf20190218_04185040/elke-spits-kent-periode-van-twijfels|publisher=HBVL|language=nl|date=18 February 2019|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref>

He then scored three consecutive goals in three matches between 6 October 2018 and 27 October 2018 against [[Royal Excel Mouscron]], [[K.V. Kortrijk]] and [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]].<ref>{{cite news|title=STVV pas in extremis voorbij negen spelers van Moeskroen|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/live/voetbal/280055|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|language=nl|date=6 October 2018|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=KV Kortrijk sluipt dichter bij top zes na zege tegen STVV|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/live/voetbal/280066|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|language=nl|date=20 October 2018|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Twee lachwekkende owngoals kosten Club Brugge ook punten in STVV|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/live/voetbal/280075|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|language=nl|date=27 October 2018|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> Kamada then scored four goals in three matches between 4 November 2018 and 25 November 2018, including a brace against [[K.A.S. Eupen|Eupen]] on 10 November 2018.<ref>{{cite news|title=Zulte Waregem gaat tegen STVV in tweede helft onderuit en staat alweer laatste|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/live/voetbal/280092|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|language=nl|date=4 November 2018|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=STVV springt dankzij ruime zege bij Eupen naar vijfde plek|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/live/voetbal/280097|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|language=nl|date=10 November 2018|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Piepjong Anderlecht gaat onderuit op Sint Truiden ondanks hoopgevende prestatie van tieners|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/live/voetbal/280104|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|language=nl|date=25 November 2018|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> He, once again, scored two goals in two matches between 5 December 2018 and 8 December 2018 against Standard Liège and KFC Mandel United.<ref>{{cite news|title=STVV bekert voort maar amateurs van Mandel hielden het 93 minuten spannend|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/live/voetbal/285810|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|language=nl|date=5 December 2018|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Oulare bezorgt Standard gelijkspel bij sterk STVV|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/live/voetbal/280122|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|language=nl|date=8 December 2018|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> By the end of the year, Kamada scored 11 goals in 17 appearances in all competitions.

Kamada had to wait until 3 February 2019 to score again in a 4–1 win against Eupen.<ref>{{cite news|title=STVV boekt simpele thuiszege tegen Eupen en knikkert Anderlecht uit top zes|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/live/voetbal/280169|website=Het Nieuwsblad|language=nl|date=3 February 2010|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> A month later on 10 March 2019, he scored his 12th goal of the season, in a 1–1 draw against [[Royal Excel Mouscron]].<ref>{{cite news|title=VERSLAG Moeskroen-STVV. Kanaries in nesten na gelijkspel tegen negen man|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/live/voetbal/280208|website=Het Nieuwsblad|language=nl|date=10 March 2019|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> In the [[2018–19 Belgian First Division A#Europa League play-offs|Group A league play-offs]], Kamada later scored three goals, including a brace, in a 2–2 draw against [[K.V.C. Westerlo|Westerlo]] on 6 April 2019.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kurt Abrahams bezorgt Westerlo punt tegen ex-ploeg STVV|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/live/voetbal/280244|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|language=nl|date=6 April 2019|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Eupen kan niet winnen: afscheidnemende Luis Garcia mist beslissende strafschop na rode kaart STVV|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/live/voetbal/280261|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|language=nl|date=20 April 2019|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> At the end of the 2018–19 season, he went on to make 36 appearances and score sixteen times in all competitions.

====Return to Eintracht Frankfurt====
[[File:FC Salzburg gegen SG Eintracht Frankfurt (28. Februar 2020 EL Sechzehntelfinale Rückspiel) 60.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Kamada pictured with [[Martin Hinteregger]] and [[Hwang Hee-chan]] prior to the second leg of [[UEFA Europa League]]'s round of 32 match against [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]].]]

Since the start of the 2019–20 season, Kamada returned from a loan spell at Sint-Truiden and quickly became a first team regular for Eintracht Frankfurt, playing as a [[second striker]].<ref name="Kamada Interview 2"/><ref>{{cite news|title= Eintracht: Deshalb kann Kamada die Überraschung der Saison werden|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-sge-daichi-kamada-greift-zr-12821515.html|publisher=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=16 July 2019|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Kamada, Toure und der Risikofaktor|url=https://www.kicker.de/kamada_toure_und_der_risikofaktor-771892/artikel|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=10 March 2020|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Kamadas komfortable Situation|url=https://www.kicker.de/kamadas_komfortable_situation-777566/artikel|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=15 June 2020|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Eintracht Frankfurt: Das sind die Strippenzieher im Mittelfeld|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-sge-strippenzieher-eintracht-frankfurt-zr-13196036.html|publisher=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=7 November 2019|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Eintracht Frankfurt vor dem nächsten Endspiel gegen SV Werder Bremen|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-sge-sv-werder-bremen-naechsten-endspiel-13784771.html|publisher=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=3 June 2020|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> He then scored his first goal of the season, in a 5–3 win against [[SV Waldhof Mannheim|Waldhof Mannheim]] in the first round of the DFB–Pokal.<ref>{{cite news|title=Hattrick im Tor-Spektakel: Rebic ballert Frankfurt weiter|url=https://www.kicker.de/mannheim-gegen-frankfurt-2019-dfb-pokal-4579324/analyse|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=12 August 2019|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> Manager [[Adi Hütter]] praised his performances, stating that Kamada has matured and presented himself differently.<ref>{{cite news|title=Lob für Kamada, Fingerzeig für Willems|url=https://www.kicker.de/lob-fuer-kamada-fingerzeig-fuer-willems-752942/artikel|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=7 August 2019|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title="Kamada wird eine sehr gute Entwicklung nehmen"|url=https://www.kicker.de/kamada-wird-eine-sehr-gute-entwicklung-nehmen-755687/artikel|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=16 August 2019|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=André Silva: Mit Nummer 17 geht der Knopf auf|url=https://www.kicker.de/andr_silva_mit_nummer_17_geht_der_knopf_auf-758533/artikel|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=23 September 2019|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> He then scored a brace in a 2–1 win against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in the UEFA Europa League match on 28 November.<ref>{{cite news|title=Arsenal 1–2 Eintracht Frankfurt|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/50578269|publisher=BBC Sport|date=28 November 2019|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> After the match, manager Hütter, once again, praised Kamada's performance for "having so much quality" by "having the ball 53 times throughout the match and completed 79 percent of his passes to teammates".<ref>{{cite news|title=Daichi Kamadas Sternstunde in Europa|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-sge-daichi-kamada-seine-sternstunde-europapokal-zr-13258021.html|publisher=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=29 November 2019|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> He then scored to take a lead in the UEFA Europa League match against [[Vitória S.C.|Vitória]] at half–time, but the club went on to lose 3–2 on 12 December 2019.<ref>{{cite news|title=Nach da Costas Slapstick-Tor: Eintracht zittert sich weiter|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-guimaraes-2019-europa-league-4612327/analyse|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=12 December 2019|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> At the beginning of 2020, Kamada suffered a torn ligament that kept him out throughout January.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kamada fällt mit Bänderriss aus – schlägt die Eintracht nochmal zu?|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-verletzungspech-daichi-kamada-reisst-loch-mittelfeld-13429021.html|publisher=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=10 January 2020|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Bänderriss bei Kamada – Hütter hofft auf zwei Verstärkungen|url=https://www.kicker.de/baenderriss_bei_kamada_huetter_hofft_auf_zwei_verstaerkungen-766805/artikel|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=9 January 2020|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> He returned to the starting line–up and played 45 minutes before being substituted, in a 1–1 draw against [[Fortuna Düsseldorf]] on 1 February 2020.<ref>{{cite news|title=90.+3! Chandler entreißt Rösler ganz spät den Premierensieg|url=https://www.kicker.de/duesseldorf-gegen-frankfurt-2020-bundesliga-4588832/analyse|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=1 February 2020|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> Against [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]] in the second leg of [[UEFA Europa League]]'s Round of 32 match, Kamada scored a hat–trick, in a 4–1 win.<ref>{{cite news|title=Eintracht Frankfurt macht den nächsten Schritt ins Ungewisse|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-kamada-dost-wieder-fit-13511149.html|publisher=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=30 January 2020|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Eintracht Frankfurt aktuell ein zahnloser Tiger|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-sge-bundesliga-fussball-zr-13543609.html|publisher=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=17 February 2020|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Kamadas Dreierpack bringt Eintracht auf Achtelfinalkurs|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-salzburg-2020-europa-league-4623971/analyse|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=20 February 2020|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> The club went on to progress to the next round of the UEFA Europa League following a 2–2 draw in the second leg.<ref>{{cite news|title=Silvas Tore kommen zum richtigen Zeitpunkt|url=https://www.kicker.de/salzburg-gegen-frankfurt-2020-europa-league-4623972/analyse|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=28 February 2020|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> He scored his eighth goal of the season, in a 2–0 win against [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]] in the quarter–finals of the DFB–Pokal on 4 March 2020.<ref>{{cite news|title=Nach VAR-Elfmeter und Kamada-Tor: Eintracht im Halbfinale|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-bremen-2020-dfb-pokal-4633206/analyse|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=4 March 2020|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> However, the season was suspended because of the [[COVID-19 pandemic in Germany|COVID-19 pandemic]] and was pushed back to two months.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Nach aktuellen Entwicklungen in Zusammenhang mit dem Corona-Virus: DFL beschließt Verlegung des 26. Spieltags der Bundesliga und 2. Bundesliga|url=https://www.dfl.de/de/aktuelles/nach-aktuellen-entwicklungen-in-zusammenhang-mit-dem-corona-virus-dfl-beschliesst-verlegung-des-26-spieltags-der-bundesliga-und-2-bundesliga/|work=[[Deutsche Fußball Liga]] |language=de|date=13 March 2020|access-date=31 August 2021}}</ref> Once the season resumed behind closed doors, Kamada then scored his ninth goal of the season, as well as, setting up the club's first goal of the game, in a 3–3 draw against SC Freiburg on 26 May.<ref>{{cite news|title=Re-Start ohne Freitagsspiel: Bundesliga geht erst am 16. Mai weiter|url=https://www.kicker.de/re_start_ohne_freitagsspiel_bundesliga_geht_erst_am_16_mai_weiter-775139/artikel|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=7 May 2020|access-date=31 August 2021}}<br>{{cite news|title=Joker Chandler macht den Wahnsinn perfekt|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-freiburg-2020-bundesliga-4588904/analyse|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=25 May 2020|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> This was followed up by scoring in a 2–1 win against [[VfL Wolfsburg]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Kamada und Silva beenden Frankfurts Negativserie|url=https://www.kicker.de/wolfsburg-gegen-frankfurt-2020-bundesliga-4588912/analyse|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=30 May 2020|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> By the end of the season, Kamada had made 48 appearances and scoring sixteen times in all competitions, making him the club's third top scorer of the season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Aufstellungen sind da: Folgende Startelf soll in Köln siegen|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-kamada-gesperrt-ueberraschende-startelf-koeln-zr-13802872.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=20 June 2020|access-date=31 August 2021}}</ref> Following this, Frankfurt began talks with the player over a new contract.<ref>{{cite news|title=Eintracht: Die Vertragssituationen der Profis und Trainer Adi Hütter|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-vertragssituationen-profis-trainer-huetter-zr-13806429.html|publisher=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=23 June 2020|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Woran es bei Kamada wirklich hakt|url=https://www.kicker.de/woran_es_bei_kamada_wirklich_hakt-779455/artikel|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=10 July 2020|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=Eintracht Frankfurt: Verhandlungen mit Kamada im Stocken – Bewegung bei Ante Rebic|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-sge-kamada-rebic-transfer-stockt-fliessen-sollte-13829911.html|publisher=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=13 July 2020|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> During the negotiation, manager Hütter wanted Kamada to stay, describing him as "a great, interesting player".<ref>{{cite news|title=Eintracht Frankfurt und der Poker um Daichi Kamada|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/der-poker-um-daichi-kamada-90022175.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=14 August 2020|access-date=31 August 2021}}<br>{{cite news|title=Ob Adi Hütter die Eintracht verlässt ist unklar – Doch der Coach rät einem Star dringend zu bleiben|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-sge-adi-huetter-vertrag-filip-kostic-90028175.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=23 August 2020|access-date=31 August 2021}}</ref>

[[File:FC Salzburg gegen SG Eintracht Frankfurt (28. Februar 2020 EL Sechzehntelfinale Rückspiel) 67.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Kamada chasing the ball during the second leg of UEFA Europa League's round of 32 match against Red Bull Salzburg.]]

Three days before the start of the 2020–21 season, Kamada signed a contract extension with Eintracht Frankfurt, keeping him until 2023, with manager Hütter played a factor to his decision.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://profis.eintracht.de/news/kamada-bleibt-ein-adlertraeger-127679/|title=Kamada bleibt ein Adlerträger|website=Eintracht Frankfurt|language=de|date=16 September 2020|access-date=31 August 2021|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200920020750/https://profis.eintracht.de/news/kamada-bleibt-ein-adlertraeger-127679|archive-date=20 September 2020|url-status=live}}<br>{{cite news|title=Daichi Kamada: Eine Rolex kaufen oder nicht?|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/daichi-kamada-das-gefuehl-gebraucht-zu-werden-90045495.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=17 August 2020|access-date=31 August 2021}}</ref> A week later against [[Hertha BSC]] on 25 September 2020, he played a key role to match by setting up two goals in a 3–1 win.<ref>{{cite news|title=Silva legt den Grundstein, Rode sorgt für die kalte Dusche|url=https://www.kicker.de/hertha-gegen-frankfurt-2020-bundesliga-4667070/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=25 September 2020|access-date=31 August 2021}}</ref> In a follow–up match against [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|Hoffenheim]], Kamada scored his first goal of the season, in a 2–1 win.<ref>{{cite news|title=Traumstart: Dost schießt Frankfurt an die Tabellenspitze|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-hoffenheim-2020-bundesliga-4667079/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=3 October 2020|access-date=31 August 2021}}</ref> Since the start of the 2020–21 season, he continued to be a first team regular, playing in the attacking midfield position.<ref>{{cite news|title=Formstarker Bas Dost treibt sich und seine Kollegen an|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/sge-eintracht-frankfurt-schreihals-mit-koepfchen-90064378.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=9 October 2020|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Frankfurts neues Trio infernale auch für Bayern gefährlich?|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurts-neues-trio-infernale-auch-fuer-bayern-gefaehrlich-787888/artikel|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=22 October 2020|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Eintracht: Adi Hütter wehrt sich gegen Kritik und warnt Profis aus der zweiten Reihe|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/das-prinzip-des-vertrauens-90097464.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=12 November 2020|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Daichi Kamada macht den dicken Max|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-daichi-kamada-union-berlin-max-kruse-90112815.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=27 November 2020|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Eintracht Frankfurt: Daichi Kamada wird immer wertvoller|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-sge-daichi-kamada-der-dem-ball-schmeichelt-90126106.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=10 December 2020|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> Kamada played a role in a match against [[1. FC Union Berlin|Union Berlin]] when he sets up two goals, as the club drew 3–3 on 28 November 2020.<ref>{{cite news|title=3:3 in Köpenick: Union hat Kruse, Frankfurt André Silva|url=https://www.kicker.de/union-gegen-frankfurt-2020-bundesliga-4667134/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=28 November 2020|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> In a follow–up match, Kamada played another role in a match against [[Borussia Dortmund]] when he scored the opening goal of the game, in a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{cite news|title=Reynas Traumtor beschert Dortmund zumindest ein Remis|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-dortmund-2020-bundesliga-4667141/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=5 December 2020|access-date=31 August 2021}}</ref> Since the start of the 2020–21 season, Kamada started in every match until he was dropped to the substitute bench for the last two matches of the year, with manager Hütter said the player needs to improve on his performance.<ref>{{cite news|title=Tiefschlag gegen Gladbach: Eintracht und die Kunst des Verdrängens|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/die-kunst-des-verdraengens-90133515.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=16 December 2020|access-date=31 August 2021}}<br>{{cite news|title=Eintracht: Hütter muss umstellen – wer ersetzt gesperrten David Abraham?|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/fragezeichen-vorne-und-hinten-90145396.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=18 December 2020|access-date=31 August 2021}}<br>{{cite news|title=Die Lehren des Endspurts|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/die-lehren-des-endspurts-90147386.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=21 December 2020|access-date=31 August 2021}}</ref> In the second half of the season, Kamada continued alternating between a starting and a substitute role despite competing with [[Amin Younes]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Mit Spielwitz und Schärfe|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-mit-spielwitz-und-schaerfe-90157346.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=3 January 2021|access-date=31 August 2021}}<br>{{cite news|title=Eintracht gegen Schalke: So könnte die Startelf mit Luka Jovic aussehen|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-sge-schalke-04-bundesliga-adi-huetter-aufstellung-90170296.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=15 January 2021|access-date=31 August 2021}}<br>{{cite news|title=Eintracht Frankfurt: Coole Auftritte voller Dominanz|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-sge-coole-auftritte-voller-dominanz-90196191.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=10 February 2021|access-date=31 August 2021}}<br>{{cite news|title=Vorne hui, hinten hui: Bei Eintracht Frankfurt passt alles|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/vorne-hui-hinten-hui-90198619.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=11 February 2021|access-date=31 August 2021}}<br>{{cite news|title=Großes Zwischenzeugnis für alle Profis im Kader der SGE|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-profis-kader-sge-zwischen-zeugnis-hinrunde-90177343.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=23 January 2021|access-date=31 August 2021}}</ref> In a match against [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] on 20 February 2021, he played a key role to the match by scoring a goal and setting up a goal for Younes, in a 2–1 win.<ref>{{cite news|title=Younes' Traumtor, Frankfurts Coup – Die Bayern stolpern|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-bayern-2021-bundesliga-4667249/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=20 February 2021|access-date=31 August 2021}}</ref> After missing one match due to lumbago, Kamada scored on his return from injury, in a 1–1 draw against [[RB Leipzig]] on 14 March.<ref>{{cite news|title=Frankfurt nur Remis gegen Aufsteiger Stuttgart|url=https://www.fr.de/sport/fussball/frankfurt-nur-remis-gegen-aufsteiger-stuttgart-zr-90231155.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=6 March 2021|access-date=31 August 2021}}<br>f{{cite news|title=Kamada kontert Forsberg: Leipzig strauchelt im Meisterrennen|url=https://www.kicker.de/leipzig-gegen-frankfurt-2021-bundesliga-4667274/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=14 March 2021|access-date=31 August 2021}}</ref> Despite scoring on his return, he played in the right–midfield position, which Manager Hütter acknowledged the negativity criticism from [[Frankfurter Rundschau]], describing it as "a failed experiment".<ref>{{cite news|title=Die Spieler von Eintracht Frankfurt in der Einzelkritik: Der rasende Ilsanker|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-spieler-in-der-einzelkritik-der-rasende-ilsanker-90241502.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=15 March 2021|access-date=31 August 2021}}<br>{{cite news|title=Eintracht Frankfurt gegen Leipzig – Adi Hütter selbstkritisch: "Das ist eher meine Schuld"|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-sge-adi-huetter-das-ist-eher-meine-schuld-90241598.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=16 March 2021|access-date=31 August 2021}}</ref> On 10 April, Kamada scored his fifth goal of the season and set up one of the goals, in a 4–3 win against VfL Wolfsburg.<ref>{{cite news|title=4:3: Frankfurt ringt Wolfsburg im Wechselbad der Gefühle nieder|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-wolfsburg-2021-bundesliga-4667302/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=10 April 2021|access-date=31 August 2021}}<br>{{cite news|title=Eintracht-Angriff furios: Keiner stoppt Jovic und Silva|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/keiner-stoppt-jovic-und-silva-90405443.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=12 April 2021|access-date=31 August 2021}}</ref> Despite failing to qualify for the [[UEFA Champions League]] [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League|next season]], his contributions saw Eintracht Frankfurt qualify for the [[UEFA Europa League]] [[2021–22 UEFA Europa League|instead]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Eintracht Frankfurt blamiert sich auf Schalke – und kann Champions League abhaken|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-blamiert-sich-auf-schalke-und-kann-champions-league-abhaken-zr-90578013.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=15 May 2021|access-date=31 August 2021}}<br>{{cite news|title=Frankfurts Joker schenken Hütter einen Sieg zum Abschied|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-freiburg-2021-bundesliga-4667358/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=22 May 2021|access-date=31 August 2021}}</ref> At the end of the 2020–21 season, he had made 34 appearances and scored five times in all competitions.<ref>{{cite news|title=Abschlusszeugnis von Eintracht Frankfurt – Note 2+|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-spieler-einzelkritik-abschlusszeugnis-2021-90659626.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=26 May 2021|access-date=31 August 2021}}</ref>

At the start of the 2021–22 season, Kamada found himself alternating between a starting and a substitute role under the new management of [[Oliver Glasner]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Eintracht: Daichi Kamada nimmt Stellung zu Wechselgerüchten|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-daichi-kamada-wechselgeruechte-sge-transfer-bundesliga-fussball-news-90897060.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=2 August 2021|access-date=31 August 2021}}<br>{{cite news|title=Eintracht Frankfurt: Glasner "nicht wirklich happy" – Umbruch größer als gedacht|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-umbruch-also-doch-90934976.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=20 August 2021|access-date=31 August 2021}}<br>{{cite news|title=Glasner: "Ich habe selten einen so spielintelligenten Spieler gesehen"|url=https://www.kicker.de/glasner-ich-habe-selten-einen-so-spielintelligenten-spieler-gesehen-871258/artikel|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=11 September 2021|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> He then scored three consecutive goals in the UEFA Europa League matches, including two separate matches against [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Eintracht mit Tempo-Fußball zur Tabellenführung|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-olympiakos-2021-europa-league-4749955/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=21 October 2021|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title= Wieder in der Nachspielzeit: Glasners Joker entscheiden Spiel in Piräus|url=https://www.kicker.de/olympiakos-gegen-frankfurt-2021-europa-league-4749952/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=4 November 2021|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Last-Minute-Eintracht schlägt wieder zu: SGE trotz spätem Pacienca-Treffer noch nicht durch|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-antwerpen-2021-europa-league-4749957/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=25 November 2021|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> He scored his first league goal of the season, which turned out to be a winning goal, in a 3–2 win against [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]] on 15 December 2021.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kamada schockt Gladbach – Trapp hält Dreier fest|url=https://www.kicker.de/mgladbach-gegen-frankfurt-2021-bundesliga-4721634/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=15 December 2021|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> Kamada scored a month later on 16 January 2022, in a 1–1 draw against [[FC Augsburg]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Kamada wie aus einem Guss – Punkteteilung in Augsburg|url=https://www.kicker.de/augsburg-gegen-frankfurt-2022-bundesliga-4721663/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=16 January 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> After missing one match due to a torn muscle fibre, Kamada returned to the starting line–up from injury, in a 2–0 loss against [[VfL Wolfsburg]] on 12 February 2022.<ref>{{cite news|title=Frankfurt muss vorerst auf Kamada verzichten|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-muss-vorerst-auf-kamada-verzichten-887818/artikel|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=27 January 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Eintracht Frankfurt: SGE muss in Stuttgart auf Kostic und Kamada verzichten|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-sge-ohne-kostic-und-kamada-zum-neustart-beim-vfb-stuttgart-91279356.htmll|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=4 February 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=SGE-Spezialist Kruse führt die Wölfe zum nächsten Sieg|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-wolfsburg-2022-bundesliga-4721685/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=12 February 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> Initially placed on the substitute bench following his return from injury, he regained his first team place for the rest of the season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Eintracht Frankfurt: Alles auf Anfang|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-alles-auf-anfang-91347608.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=15 February 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Die Torlos-Eintracht|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/die-torlos-eintracht-91376231.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=27 February 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Gesicht des Aufschwungs: Kamadas frappierende Antwort|url=https://www.kicker.de/gesicht-des-aufschwungs-kamadas-frappierende-antwort-894049/artikel|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=7 March 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> Kamada scored two goals in two matches between 9 March 2022 and 13 March 2022, which were winning goals against [[Real Betis]] and [[VfL Bochum]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Borré verpasst sogar noch mehr: Frankfurt gewinnt Hinspiel in Sevilla|url=https://www.kicker.de/betis-gegen-frankfurt-2022-europa-league-4766839/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=9 March 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Negativrekord abgewendet: Frankfurt dreht Spiel dank Doppelschlag|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-bochum-2022-bundesliga-4721721/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=13 March 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> On 14 April 2022, he set up one of the goals for [[Filip Kostić]] as the club defeated [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] 3–2 at the [[Camp Nou]] and 4–3 on aggregate in the [[2021–22 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]] to qualify for the [[2021–22 UEFA Europa League knockout phase|semi-finals]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/apr/14/eintrachy-frankfurt-filip-kostic-doubles-up-to-dump-barcelona-out-of-europa-league|title=Frankfurt's Filip Kostic doubles up to dump Barcelona out of Europa League|date=14 April 2022|work=The Guardian|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> Kamada, once again, scored two goals in two matches, including scoring the winning goal in a 2–1 win over [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] in the first leg of the semi-finals of the [[2021–22 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] on 28 April 2022.<ref>{{cite news|title=Rutter hat das letzte Wort: Hoffenheim nimmt einen Punkt aus Frankfurt mit|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-hoffenheim-2022-bundesliga-4721768/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=23 April 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/apr/28/west-ham-eintracht-frankfurt-europa-league-match-report|title=West Ham face uphill task after Kamada rewards Eintracht Frankfurt dominance|work=The Guardian|date=28 April 2022|access-date=19 May 2022}}</ref> Eventually, Eintracht Frankfurt won the tournament after beating [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] 5–4 on penalty shootouts in the [[2022 UEFA Europa League Final|final]], in which he scored one of them.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/eintracht-frankfurt-s-unbeaten-run-to-winning-the-europa-league-barcelona-rangers-20045|title=Eintracht Frankfurt's unbeaten run to winning the UEFA Europa League|website=Bundesliga |date=21 May 2022}}</ref> At the end of the 2021–22 season, Kamada made 46 appearances and scoring nine times in all competitions.

[[File:DaichiKamada.jpg|thumb|left|190px|Kamada playing for [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] in 2019.]]

Kamada started the 2022–23 season well when he scored four goals in the first month to the season, including a brace against [[1. FC Magdeburg]] in the first round of DFB–Pokal.<ref>{{cite news|title=Doppelpack Kamada: Frankfurt bestraft mutiges Magdeburg gnadenlos|url=https://www.kicker.de/magdeburg-gegen-frankfurt-2022-dfb-pokal-4774112/spielbericht|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=1 August 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Kamada kontert Serdar – Schiedsrichter Willenborg spät im Fokus|url=https://www.kicker.de/hertha-gegen-frankfurt-2022-bundesliga-4781447/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=13 August 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Thielmann kontert Kamada: Köln verlängert Frankfurter Misere|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-koeln-2022-bundesliga-4781454/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=21 August 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> The performance also earned the trust of manager Glasner, who continued to give him a place in the first team.<ref>{{cite news|title=Roulette bei der SGE – Aus sechs mach drei|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/drei-eintracht-roulette-aus-sechs-mach-91675920.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=21 July 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Glasner vor der Wahl: Wohin mit Kamada?|url=https://www.kicker.de/glasner-vor-der-wahl-wohin-mit-kamada-911794/artikel|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=4 August 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Setzt Glasner auf Kamada und Götze?|url=https://www.kicker.de/setzt-glasner-auf-kamada-und-goetze-914902/artikel|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=27 August 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Borre, Turay & Co.: Die aktuellen Eintracht-Gerüchte in der Übersicht|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-transfer-news-geruechte-wechsel-borre-turay-fussball-bundesliga-91848926.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=14 October 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Daichi Kamada galt schon als gescheitert – Dann kam Glasner zu Eintracht Frankfurt|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/daichi-kamada-eintracht-frankfurt-fussball-bundesliga-europapokal-91872136.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=24 October 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> Kamada then scored two more goals throughout September, coming against [[VfB Stuttgart]] and [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Kolo Muani and Götze excel: Frankfurt beats Leipzig 4–0|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-leipzig-2022-bundesliga-4781472/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=3 September 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Kamada stets beteiligt: Frankfurt siegt in Stuttgart durch Standards|url=https://www.kicker.de/stuttgart-gegen-frankfurt-2022-bundesliga-4781494/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=17 September 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> Between 15 October 2022 and 1 November 2022, he scored a total of six goals in all competitions, including [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League group stage|the UEFA Champions League group stage]] when he scored in the last three consecutive matches against [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]], [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] and [[Sporting CP]], which helped his club to reach the [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|knockout phase]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Dank Sons Doppelpack: Tottenham bezwingt die Eintracht|url=https://www.kicker.de/tottenham-gegen-frankfurt-2022-champions-league-4815263/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=12 October 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=5:1! Lindström und Kolo Muani wirbeln Leverkusens Defensive durcheinander|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-leverkusen-2022-bundesliga-4781517/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=15 October 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Doppelpass hebelt Marseille aus: Frankfurt wahrt den Achtelfinal-Traum|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-marseille-2022-champions-league-4815262/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=26 October 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Schlüsselszene: Frankfurt bekommt klaren Elfmeter nicht – und der BVB siegt|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-dortmund-2022-bundesliga-4781535/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=29 October 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Eintracht in Ekstase: Kolo Muani schießt Frankfurt ins Achtelfinale|url=https://www.kicker.de/sp-lissabon-gegen-frankfurt-2022-champions-league-4815266/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=1 November 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite web|title=Not Haaland, nor Lewandowski: This Japanese player has the best scoring rate in Europe's top five leagues|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/champions-league/2022/11/03/6363e65c46163f01a68b45a3.html|website=Marca|date=3 November 2022}}</ref> After missing one match due to an illness in early–November, Kamada returned to the starting line–up against [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|Hoffenheim]] on 9 November 2022 and set up one of the goals, in a 4–2 win.<ref>{{cite news|title=Duell der Notenbesten fällt aus: Wen Gikiewicz und Kamada toppen|url=https://www.kicker.de/duell-der-notenbesten-faellt-aus-wen-gikiewicz-und-kamada-toppen-924255/artikel|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=5 November 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Götze, Lindström und Kolo Muani zaubern gegen Hoffenheim|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-hoffenheim-2022-bundesliga-4781553/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=9 November 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref>

Following the World Cup, he regained his first team place and began rotating in either centre–midfield position and attacking midfield position.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kamada verbreitet Angst und Schrecken|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/kamada-verbreitet-angst-und-schrecken-91928918.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=21 November 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Eintracht Frankfurt: Das Puzzle in der Defensive|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-das-puzzle-in-der-defensive-92114738.html|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=28 February 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Eintracht Frankfurt: Das Pfeifen am Scheunentor|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-das-pfeifen-am-scheunentor-92122269.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=3 March 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Eintracht Frankfurt: Einsatzgarantie für Rafael Borré|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-einsatzgarantie-fuer-rafael-borre-92135053.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=9 March 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Das große Eintracht-Zeugnis: Note 2-|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/zeugnis-note-das-grosse-eintracht-92326035.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=8 June 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> Kamada had to wait until 7 February 2023 when he scored in the last 16 of the DFB–Pokal, in a 4–2 win against [[SV Darmstadt 98]].<ref>{{cite news |date=7 February 2023 |title=Kolo Muani früh und spät: Frankfurt gewinnt packendes Pokal-Derby |trans-title=Kolo Muani early and late: Frankfurt wins thrilling cup derby. |url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-darmstadt-2023-dfb-pokal-4822978/analyse |access-date=7 September 2024 |website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]] |language=de}}</ref> However, Kamada faced criticism by Frankfurter Rundschau for his lack of form, which saw him struggle to score goals.<ref>{{cite news|title=Eintracht: Zwischen Tristesse und leiser Hoffnung|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/leiser-hoffnung-eintracht-zwischen-tristesse-und-92201603.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=12 April 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Eintracht Frankfurt und das Rätsel Daichi Kamada|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/raetsel-daichi-kamada-eintracht-frankfurt-und-das-92206151.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=15 April 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Aaronson und Alidou überzeugen: Zeit, dass sich was dreht|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/was-dreht-aaronson-und-alidou-ueberzeugen-zeit-dass-sich-92214175.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=18 April 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> In the semi–finals of the DFB–Pokal, he scored his first goal in almost three months, in a 3–2 win against Stuttgart to help Eintracht Frankfurt reach [[2023 DFB-Pokal final|the final]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Kolo Muani, Ndicka und Kamada führen Frankfurt ins Pokalfinale|url=https://www.kicker.de/stuttgart-gegen-frankfurt-2023-dfb-pokal-4842031/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=3 May 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> After the match, Frankfurter Rundschau, who have been critical of Kamada's performance, reviewed positively towards his performance.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kamada, Ndicka und Kolo Muani brauchen Anlauf|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/kamada-braucht-anlauf-92253410.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=4 May 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Eintracht und die speziellen Momente|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/momente-eintracht-und-die-speziellen-92254193.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=5 May 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> He then scored two goals in two matches between 13 May 2023 and 20 May 2023 against [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]] and [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Butas herrlicher Knaller: Frankfurt schlägt und überholt Mainz|url=https://www.kicker.de/frankfurt-gegen-mainz-2023-bundesliga-4781716/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=13 May 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Joker Polter sichert immerhin noch ein 2:2 gegen Frankfurt|url=https://www.kicker.de/schalke-gegen-frankfurt-2023-bundesliga-4781727/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=20 May 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Eintracht greift noch mal an|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/noch-mal-an-eintracht-frankfurt-greift-92286535.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=21 May 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> Kamada made his last appearance for the club, starting the match, in a 2–0 loss against RB Leipzig in the DFB–Pokal final.<ref>{{cite news|title=Matchwinner Nkunku: RB Leipzig gewinnt erneut den DFB-Pokal|url=https://www.kicker.de/leipzig-gegen-frankfurt-2023-dfb-pokal-4844336/analyse|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=6 June 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Pokal-Einzelkritik: Dumm gelaufen, Eintracht – Ndicka fälscht entscheidend ab|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/dumm-gelaufen-eintracht-frankfurt-dfb-pokal-ndicka-faelscht-entscheidend-ab-92321117.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=4 June 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> At the end of the 2022–23 season, he made 47 appearances and scoring 16 times in all competitions. Between 2022 and 2023, Kamada's future at Eintracht Frankfurt was speculated by local newspaper. Frankfurter Rundschau, with his contract expiring at the end of the 2022–23 season.<ref>{{cite news |date=19 February 2022 |title=Daichi Kamada steht bei Eintracht Frankfurt auf der Kippe |trans-title=Daichi Kamada is on the verge of leaving Eintracht Frankfurt. |url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/kamada-steht-bei-eintracht-frankfurt-auf-der-kippe-91357473.html |access-date=7 September 2024 |website=Frankfurter Rundschau |language=de}}<br />{{cite news |date=21 February 2022 |title=az888 |url=https://az8-88.mx/ |access-date=7 September 2024 |website=Frankfurter Rundschau |language=de}}<br />{{cite news |date=3 March 2022 |title=Eintracht Frankfurt: Was ist nur mit Kamada und Kostic los? |trans-title=Eintracht Frankfurt: What is going on with Kamada and Kostic? |url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/was-ist-nur-mit-kostic-kamada-los-91381061.html |access-date=7 September 2024 |website=Frankfurter Rundschau |language=de}}</ref> This led to Eintracht Frankfurt began opening a contract negotiations in effort to keep the player.<ref>{{cite news |date=10 July 2022 |title=Eintracht Frankfurt: Bleiben die begehrten Drei womöglich doch? |trans-title=Eintracht Frankfurt: Could the coveted three possibly stay after all? |url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-bleiben-die-begehrten-drei-womoeglich-doch-91658727.html |access-date=7 September 2024 |website=Frankfurter Rundschau |language=de}}<br />{{cite news |date=23 February 2023 |title=Auslaufende Verträge: So sieht die Zukunft der Eintracht-Spieler aus |trans-title=Expiring Contracts: This is the future of the Eintracht players. |url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-kader-auslaufende-vertraege-sge-spieler-zukunft-92105423.html |access-date=7 September 2024 |website=Frankfurter Rundschau |language=de}}<br />{{cite news |date=22 February 2023 |title=Chemie-Nobelpreismedaille für Kamada? |trans-title=Chemistry Nobel Prize Medal for Kamada? |url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-daichi-kamada-chemie-nobelpreis-medaille-sge-news-92103236.html |access-date=7 September 2024 |website=Frankfurter Rundschau |language=de}}</ref> He was linked with a move to European clubs, such as, [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]], [[Borussia Dortmund]], [[FC Barcelona]] and [[Atlético Madrid]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Glasner erleichtert: "Kamada bleibt bei uns"|url=https://www.kicker.de/glasner-erleichtert-kamada-bleibt-bei-uns-915092/artikel|website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|language=de|date=29 August 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Bundesligist und Premier-League-Klub an Eintracht-Star dran|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-star-begehrt-von-bundesligist-und-premier-league-klub-91964332.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=8 December 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Dortmund oder Barcelona? Kamada könnte Frankfurt bald verlassen|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/fc-barcelona-kamada-eintracht-frankfurt-musterschueler-sprung-bvb-91977570.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=19 December 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Doch kein Wechsel zum BVB: Eintracht-Star Kamada zieht es nach Spanien|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/wechsel-spanien-news-wechsel-sge-bvb-eintracht-star-kamada-transfer-92194756.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=8 April 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> It was confirmed on 13 April 2023 that Kamada would be leaving the club.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kamada vor dem Absprung bei Eintracht Frankfurt|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/absprung-zum-bvb-eintracht-frankfurt-borussia-dortmund-daichi-kamada-vor-dem-92105747.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=26 February 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Abgang offenbar fix: Eintracht verliert Star ablösefrei|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-kamada-wechsel-fix-fussball-sport-92184532.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=2 April 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Eintracht bestätigt Abgang von Kamada – "Wünschen ihm alles Gute"|url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-bestaetigt-abgang-offensivspieler-kamada-news-92206357.html|website=Frankfurter Rundschau|language=de|date=13 April 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref>

===Lazio===
On 3 August 2023, [[Serie A]] club [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]] announced that Kamada had arrived in [[Rome]] to complete his transfer to the club on a [[Free transfer (association football)|free transfer]],<ref>{{cite web|date=3 August 2023|title=L'arrivo di Daichi Kamada a Roma|url=https://www.sslazio.it/it/news/eventi/l-arrivo-di-daichi-kamada-a-roma|publisher=S.S. Lazio|language=it|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20230804151235/https://www.sslazio.it/it/news/eventi/l-arrivo-di-daichi-kamada-a-roma|archive-date=4 August 2023|url-status=live|access-date=4 August 2023}}</ref> after his contract with Eintracht Frankfurt had not been renewed,<ref>{{Cite news|date=2023-08-04|title=Japan midfielder Kamada moves to Lazio on free transfer|language=en|work=Reuters|url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/japan-midfielder-kamada-moves-lazio-free-transfer-2023-08-04/|access-date=2023-08-19}}</ref> for a reported two-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://football-italia.net/report-lazio-agree-contract-with-kamada/|title=Report: Lazio agree contract with Kamada|publisher=Football Italia|date=2 August 2023}}</ref> On the next day, he officially joined the club, pending the entry visa to Italy.<ref>{{cite web |date=4 August 2023 |title=Daichi Kamada è un nuovo calciatore biancoceleste |trans-title=Daichi Kamada is a new player for Lazio. |url=https://www.sslazio.it/it/news/comunicati/daichi-kamada-e-un-nuovo-calciatore-biancoceleste |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20230804185154/https://www.sslazio.it/it/news/comunicati/daichi-kamada-e-un-nuovo-calciatore-biancoceleste |archive-date=4 August 2023 |publisher=S.S. Lazio |language=it |access-date=4 August 2023 }}</ref>

Kamada made his debut for Lazio, starting a match and played 54 minutes before being substituted, in a 2–1 loss against [[US Lecce]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Lecce-Lazio 2–1: ribaltone finale con Almqvist e Di Francesco|url=https://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/serie-a/2023/08/20/news/lecce_lazio_gol-411797888/|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=20 August 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> On 2 September, he scored his first goal in a 2–1 away victory over [[SSC Napoli|Napoli]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://football-italia.net/serie-a-napoli-1-2-lazio-sarri-stuns-champions-of-italy/|title=Serie A {{!}} Napoli 1–2 Lazio: Sarri stuns Champions of Italy |publisher=Football Italia |date=2 September 2023}}<br>{{cite news|title=Napoli-Lazio 1–2: Luis Alberto e Kamada regalano la prima vittoria in campionato all'ex Sarri|url=https://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/serie-a/napoli/2023/09/02/news/napoli_lazio_gol_risultato-413102523/|website=La Repubblica|language=it|date=2 September 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> However, Kamada underperformed under the management of [[Maurizio Sarri]], as Sarri putting Kamada in the winger position proved to be ineffective, as he struggled to score goals, as he failed produced it as he did at Eintracht Frankfurt.<ref>{{cite news|title=Lazio avvio shock, Sarri si difende: "I nuovi arrivati sono fuori condizione"|url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Lazio/28-08-2023/lazio-avvio-shock-sarri-si-difende-i-nuovi-arrivati-sono-fuori-condizione.shtml|website=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=it|date=28 August 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Lazio, che succede agli esterni? Pochi spunti, pochi gol: le ali deludono Sarri|url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Lazio/13-11-2023/lazio-le-ali-deludono-da-felipe-anderson-a-pedro.shtml|website=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=it|date=13 November 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Lazio, Kamada proprio non va. Sarri spiega il motivo…|url=https://www.corrieredellosport.it/news/calcio/serie-a/lazio/2023/12/30-119639234/lazio_kamada_proprio_non_va_sarri_spiega_il_motivo_|website=Corriere Dello Sport|language=it|date=30 December 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Il Messaggero: "Lotito a Sarri: dov'è Kamada?" Il giapponese in panchina da 4 partite|url=https://www.tuttomercatoweb.com/rassegna-stampa/i-il-messaggero-i-lotito-a-sarri-dov-e-kamada-il-giapponese-in-panchina-da-4-partite-1929345|website=Tutto Mercato Web|language=it|date=31 January 2024|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> With his playing time coming from the substitute bench, Kamada was linked with a move to [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] in the January [[transfer window]], but the move fell through, due to the club's CEO [[Claudio Lotito]] demanded 10 million euros, as well as, the player, himself, wanted to stay at Lazio.<ref>{{cite news|title=Lazio, su Kamada piomba il Galatasaray. Giapponese poco convinto, Lotito chiede 10 milioni|url=https://www.tuttomercatoweb.com/serie-a/lazio-su-kamada-piomba-il-galatasaray-giapponese-poco-convinto-lotito-chiede-10-milioni-1924461|website=Tutto Mercato Web|language=it|date=18 January 2024|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> But following the departure of Sarri, Kamada soon got more playing time under the new management of [[Igor Tudor]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Tudor spiega le difficoltà di Kamada alla Lazio: la differenza con Sarri|url=https://www.goal.com/it/liste/tudor-spiega-le-difficolta-di-kamada-alla-lazio-la-differenza-con-sarri/bltba713afb7790a354#csdc551d9cbc302346|website=Goal.com|language=it|date=30 March 2024|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Tudor: "Spero che i tifosi si divertano, ma conta vincere. E i miei sono sempre i più forti"|url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Lazio/05-04-2024/tudor-spero-che-i-tifosi-si-divertano-ma-conta-vincere.shtml|website=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=it|date=5 April 2024|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=Tudor: "Inzaghi straordinario all'Inter, dovremo dare l'anima. In porta c'è Provedel, è il titolare"|url=https://www.cittaceleste.it/news/lazio-giordano-kamada-bravo-tudor-ma-con-guendouzi/|website=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=it|date=18 May 2024|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> He then scored his second goal for the club, in a 1–1 draw against [[Inter Milan]] on 18 May 2024.<ref>{{cite news|title=Tudor: "Inzaghi straordinario all'Inter, dovremo dare l'anima. In porta c'è Provedel, è il titolare"|url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Lazio/18-05-2024/inter-lazio-tudor-in-conferenza-stampa.shtml|website=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=it|date=18 May 2024|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=La Lazio s'illude con Kamada, l'Inter la riprende con Dumfries all'87': poi è solo festa scudetto|url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/19-05-2024/inter-lazio-1-1-kamada-dumfries.shtml|website=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=it|date=19 May 2024|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> At the end of the 2023–24 season, Kamada went on to make 38 appearances and scoring two times in all competitions.

By the end of the [[2023–24 SS Lazio season|2023–24 season]], Lazio CEO [[Claudio Lotito]] claimed that Kamada had demanded a bonus of [[€]]2.5 million to extend his contract for another year, while declaring that he would "send away all the players who turn out to be mercenaries".<ref>{{cite web |date=2 June 2024|title=Daichi Kamada branded a 'mercenary' by Lazio CEO Claudio Lotito|url=https://onefootball.com/de/news/daichi-kamada-branded-a-mercenary-by-lazio-ceo-claudio-lotito-39573648|access-date=2 June 2024|publisher=OneFootball}}</ref> The player later confirmed that he would not renew his contract with the club, stating that "he did not care about the money" during the talks.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Football: Daichi Kamada confirms leaving Lazio, mum about next destination – The Mainichi |url=https://mainichi.jp/english/articles/20240604/p2g/00m/0sp/003000c |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240608211243/https://mainichi.jp/english/articles/20240604/p2g/00m/0sp/003000c |archive-date=8 June 2024 |access-date=2025-04-12 |work=The Mainichi |language=en-US |url-status=dead }}</ref> Upon leaving Lazio, Kamada said: "When I arrived at Lazio I felt that everyone expected a lot from me. Everyone is passionate about [[football in Italy]] and it's beautiful. But for me it was difficult above all because I arrived at the team where the best midfielder in Serie A played, [[Sergej Milinković-Savić]]. And I had to take his place. So everyone expected a lot from me in matches, but also during training. I felt that a normal performance from me wasn't enough."<ref>{{cite news |date=16 July 2024 |title=Kamada: "Potevo lasciare la Lazio già a gennaio. Per me è stata dura essere il dopo Milinkovic" |trans-title=Kamada: "I could have left Lazio as early as January. It was tough for me to be the successor to Milinkovic." |url=https://www.tuttomercatoweb.com/serie-a/kamada-potevo-lasciare-la-lazio-gia-a-gennaio-per-me-e-stata-dura-essere-il-dopo-milinkovic-1990629 |access-date=7 September 2024 |website=Tutto Mercato |language=it}}</ref>

=== Crystal Palace ===
On 1 July 2024, Kamada officially joined [[Premier League]] club [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] on a free transfer, signing a two-year contract with the club, while also became the first-ever Japanese player in the club's history.<ref name="Kamada CPFC">{{Cite web |date=1 July 2024 |title=Daichi Kamada signs for Crystal Palace |url=https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/announcement/daichi-kamada-signs-for-crystal-palace/ |access-date=1 July 2024 |website=Crystal Palace F.C.|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20240701092942/https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/announcement/daichi-kamada-signs-for-crystal-palace/|archive-date=1 July 2024|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Kamada BBC">{{Cite web|date=1 July 2024|title=Crystal Palace sign Japan midfielder Daichi Kamada on free transfer|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c51yx4g5n99o|access-date=1 July 2024|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> The move also saw him reunite with manager Glasner.<ref name="Kamada CPFC"/><ref name="Kamada BBC"/><ref>{{cite news|title=Kamada's rollercoaster journey to link up with Glasner again|url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/4038703|website=Premier League|date=1 July 2024|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref>

He made his debut for Crystal Palace, starting a match and played 65 minutes before being substituted, in a 2–1 loss against [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]] in the opening game of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/match-reports/brentford-crystal-palace-live-blog-match-report-highlights-reaction/|title=Report: Palace narrowly beaten at Brentford in Premier League opener|website=Crystal Palace F.C.|date=18 August 2024|access-date=7 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20240818163709/https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/match-reports/brentford-crystal-palace-live-blog-match-report-highlights-reaction/|archive-date=18 August 2024|url-status=live}}</ref> In doing so, Kamada became the 1000th player to make his debut for the club.<ref>{{Cite web|date=20 August 2024|title=Kamada becomes Palace's 1000th player since joining Football League|url=https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/club/daichi-kamada-crystal-palace-1000-players/|access-date=29 August 2024|website=[[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20240819175519/https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/club/daichi-kamada-crystal-palace-1000-players/|archive-date=19 August 2024|url-status=live}}</ref> Two weeks later on 27 August 2024, he scored his first goal for the Eagles and set up a goal for [[Jean-Philippe Mateta]], who set up a goal for him, in a 4–0 win against [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] in the second round of the League Cup.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/match-reports/match-report-highlights-live-blog-crystal-palace-norwich-city-august-2024/|title=Report: Eagles cruise past Canaries into Third Round|website=Crystal Palace F.C.|date=27 August 2024|access-date=7 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20240827215410/https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/match-reports/match-report-highlights-live-blog-crystal-palace-norwich-city-august-2024/|archive-date=27 August 2024|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 17 May 2025, Kamada won the [[FA Cup]] as Crystal Palace beat [[Manchester City]] 1–0 in the [[2025 FA Cup final]] for Crystal Palace's first major trophy; Kamada (along with Mateta and [[Daniel Muñoz (footballer)|Daniel Muñoz]]) helped to set up [[Eberechi Eze]]'s winning goal in the 16th minute of the game.<ref>{{cite news |title=Football: Kamada helps Palace claim 1st major trophy with FA Cup win |url=https://english.kyodonews.net/news/2025/05/5d18a79d3d7f-football-kamada-helps-palace-claim-1st-major-trophy-with-fa-cup-win.html |access-date=18 May 2025 |work=[[Kyodo News]] |ref=18 May 2025 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20250518111635/https://english.kyodonews.net/news/2025/05/5d18a79d3d7f-football-kamada-helps-palace-claim-1st-major-trophy-with-fa-cup-win.html |archive-date=18 May 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth career===
Having previously called up to the [[Japan national football team|Japan]]'s youth team for the rest of 2015, Kamada was called up to the U21 squad in August 2015.<ref>{{cite news |date=18 August 2015 |title=２３日から京都でＵ―２２日本代表候補合宿 |trans-title=The U-22 Japan national team candidates will have a training camp in Kyoto starting from the 23rd. |url=https://www.sponichi.co.jp/soccer/news/2015/08/18/kiji/K20150818010960690.html |access-date=7 September 2024 |website=Sponichi Annex |language=ja}}<br />{{cite news |date=26 August 2015 |title=U U-22日本代表 京都でのトレーニングキャンプ3日目 |url=https://www.jfa.jp/news/00007221/ |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Japan Football Association |language=ja}}<br />{{cite news |date=25 August 2015 |title=U-22日本代表 京都でのトレーニングキャンプ2日目 |url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u22_2015/news/00007211/ |access-date=7 September 2024 |website=Japan Football Association |language=ja}}<br />{{cite news |date=27 August 2015 |title=U-22日本代表 京都サンガと練習試合を行い、キャンプを打ち上げる |url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u22_2015/news/00007228/ |access-date=7 September 2024 |website=Japan Football Association |language=ja}}<br />{{cite news |date=30 October 2015 |title=U-22日本代表候補 サガン鳥栖に7–0で完勝し、キャンプを打ち上げる |url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u22_2015/news/00007773/ |access-date=7 September 2024 |website=Japan Football Association |language=ja}}</ref> He went on to make two appearances for the U21 side.

In March 2016, Kamada was called up to the [[Japan national under-23 football team|Japan U23]] squad for the first time.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sagan-tosu.net/news/p/1079/|title=牲川歩見選手 鎌田大地選手 U-23日本代表 ポルトガル遠征 メンバー選出のお知らせ|website=Sagan Tosu|language=ja|date=14 March 2016|access-date=7 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129191420/http://sagan-tosu.net/news/p/1079/|archive-date=29 November 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> He made his Japan U23 debut, coming on as a 65th-minute substitute, in a 2–1 win against [[Mexico national under-23 football team|Mexico U23]] on 25 March 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=U-23日本代表 ロンドン五輪優勝国メキシコを2－1で撃破！|url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u23_2016/news/00009275/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=25 March 2016|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> In May 2016, Kamada was called up to the Japan U23 squad for the [[2016 Toulon Tournament|Toulon Tournament]] once again.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sagan-tosu.net/news/p/1243/|title=三丸拡選手 鎌田大地選手 U-23日本代表「第44回トゥーロン国際大会(フランス)」 メンバー選出のお知らせ|website=Sagan Tosu|language=ja|date=13 May 2016|access-date=7 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20220812182814/https://sagan-tosu.net/news/p/1243/|archive-date=12 August 2022|url-status=live}}</ref> Kamada made his first start for the Japan U23 side, and played 64 minutes before being substituted, in a 2–1 win against [[Guinea national football team|Guinea U23]] on 25 May 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=U U-23日本代表 ギニアを下して今大会初勝利！|url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/news/00009913/|publisher=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=25 May 2016|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> Kamada went on to make four appearances for Japan U23, with two other matches he featured were substitute.<ref>{{cite news|title=U-23日本代表 連敗も、「前への姿勢」を貫く|url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u23_2016/toulontournament_2016/news/00009899/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=24 May 2016|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=U-23日本代表 1勝3敗で第44回トゥーロン国際大会を終える|url=https://www.jfa.jp/national_team/u23_2016/toulontournament_2016/news/00009931/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=28 May 2016|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref>

===Senior career===
Having previously failed to make a cut to the Samurai Blue squad for the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]], it was announced on 15 March 2019 that Kamada was called up to the [[Japan national football team|Japan squad]] for the first time.<ref>{{cite news|title=鎌田、初のサッカー日本代表|url=https://www.saga-s.co.jp/articles/-/349596|publisher=Saga S|language=ja|date=15 March 2019|access-date=19 July 2020}}<br>{{cite news|title=STVV verliest twee Japanners in januari door Asian Cup, revelatie Kamada haalt selectie niet|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20181212_04028636|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|language=nl|date=12 December 2018|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> He made his debut for the Samurai Blue on 22 March 2019 in a friendly against Colombia, as a 79th-minute substitute for [[Takumi Minamino]].<ref>{{cite news|title= SAMURAI BLUE、好機活かせず 森保監督就任後、初の無得点で敗れる～キリンチャレンジカップ2019（3/22＠神奈川 vsコロンビア代表）～|url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/20190322/news/00020839/|publisher=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=22 March 2019|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> Kamada then scored his first Japan goal, in a 6–0 win against [[Mongolia national football team|Mongolia]] on 10 October 2019.<ref name="Kamada Mongolia">{{cite news |date=10 October 2019 |title=森保日本６発快勝、モンゴル撃破／Ｗ杯２次予選詳細 |trans-title=Moriyasu's Japan wins 6–0, defeating Mongolia / World Cup 2nd round qualifiers details. |url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201910100000497.html |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Nikkan Sports |language=ja}}</ref>

Almost a year later, in October 2020, Kamada was called up to the Samurai Blue squad.<ref>{{cite news|title=SAMURAI BLUE（日本代表）メンバー・スケジュール ～国際親善試合 カメルーン代表戦（10/9）コートジボワール代表戦（10/13）＠ユトレヒト／Stadion Galgenwaard）～|url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/20201013/news/00025418/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=1 October 2020|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=日本代表の背番号が決定。中島翔哉不在で南野拓実が10番、鎌田大地が9番に|url=https://www.footballchannel.jp/2020/10/06/post392001/|website=Football Channel|language=ja|date=6 October 2020|access-date=31 August 2021}}<br>{{cite news|title=南野拓実が代表10番！鎌田９、久保建英17／一覧|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/202010060000931.html|website=Nikkan Sports|language=ja|date=6 October 2020|access-date=31 August 2021}}</ref> He made his first appearance in almost a year, coming on as a 71st-minute substitute, in a 0–0 draw against [[Cameroon national football team|Cameroon]] on 14 October 2020.<ref>{{cite news |date=14 October 2020 |title=SAMURAI BLUE、終了間際の植田選手の代表初ゴールでコートジボワールに勝利 |trans-title=SAMURAI BLUE wins against Ivory Coast with Ueda's first international goal in the final moments. |url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/20201013/news/00025504/ |access-date=18 August 2024 |website=Japan Football Association |language=ja}}</ref> Kamada then scored three goals in three matches for Japan between 25 March 2021 and 28 May 2021 against [[South Korea national football team|South Korea]], [[Mongolia national football team|Mongolia]] and [[Myanmar national football team|Myanmar]].<ref name="Kamada South Korea">{{cite news|title=Samurai Blue 韓国代表に3–0快勝|url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/news/00026593/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=26 March 2021|access-date=31 August 2021}}</ref><ref name="Kamada Mongolia 2">{{cite news |date=31 March 2021 |title=日本、W杯予選最多14ゴールでモンゴルに大勝！ 無傷の5連勝で最終予選進出に王手 |trans-title=Japan wins big against Mongolia with a record 14 goals in the World Cup qualifiers! With an unblemished 5 consecutive victories, they are on the brink of advancing to the final qualifiers. |url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20210330/1242763.html |access-date=31 August 2021 |website=Soccer King |language=ja}}</ref><ref name="Kamada Myanmar">{{cite news|title=大迫が圧巻5ゴール！ 南野は6戦連発、日本代表がミャンマーに10得点圧勝で最終予選進出|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20210528/1533996.html|website=Soccer King|language=ja|date=28 May 2021|access-date=31 August 2021}}<br>{{cite news|title=鎌田大地が日本代表戦で"ダメ出し"した理由。Ｗ杯ベスト８の"その先"を描く頭脳|url=https://real-sports.jp/page/articles/539675580308652859/|website=Real Sports|language=ja|date=29 June 2021|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> In May 2022, he was called up to the Samurai Blue's squad for the [[2022 Kirin Cup Soccer|Kirin Cup Soccer]].<ref>{{cite news|title=ブラジル戦など4連戦に臨む日本代表メンバー28名が発表！ 伊藤洋輝が初招集|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20220520/1650133.html|website=Soccer King|language=ja|date=29 May 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> Prior to the tournament, Kamada scored his first goal in over a year, and set one of the goals, in a 4–1 win against [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]].<ref name="Kamada Paraguay">{{cite news|title=【Match Report】SAMURAI BLUE、パラグアイ代表に4得点の快勝で4連戦を白星スタート|url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/news/00029734/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=3 June 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> He played once for Japan in the tournament, as the Samurai Blue loss 3–0 against [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia]].<ref>{{cite news|title=【Match Report】SAMURAI BLUE、チュニジア代表に後半3失点でキリンカップ優勝を逃す|url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/news/00029839/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=15 June 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> Three months later on 23 September 2022, Kamada scored once again, in a 2–0 win against [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]].<ref name="Kamada USA">{{cite news|title=日本代表がアメリカ代表に2発快勝！ 先制点の鎌田大地が躍動、三笘薫がトドメの追加点|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20220923/1691894.html|website=Soccer King|language=ja|date=23 September 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref>

On 1 November 2022, Kamada was named in the final squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar.<ref>{{cite news|title=FIFAワールドカップカタール2022™ SAMURAI BLUE（日本代表）メンバー|url=https://www.jfa.jp/news/00030869/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=1 November 2022|access-date=1 November 2022}}</ref> He made his World Cup debut, starting a match, in Japan's 2–1 win over [[Germany national football team|Germany]].<ref>{{cite news|title=【Match Report】SAMURAI BLUE、ドイツに歴史的な逆転勝利で白星発進|url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/worldcup_2022/news/00031096/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=24 November 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> He was in the starting eleven squad when the Samurai Blues win 2–1 over [[Spain national football team|Spain]] to help his country reached the knockout phase.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/daichi-kamada-maya-yoshida-japan-s-core-ready-for-germany-world-cup-clash-21963|title=Daichi Kamada, Maya Yoshida and Japan's Bundesliga core that reached the World Cup knockout stage|publisher=Bundesliga|date=1 December 2022}}<br>{{cite news|title=World Cup 2022 – Germany 1–2 Japan: Late Ritsu Doan and Takuma Asano goals earn shock victory|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/12098/12753787/world-cup-2022-germany-1-2-japan-late-ritsu-doan-and-takuma-asano-goals-earn-shock-victory|website=Sky Sports|date=24 November 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> In the last-16 of the World Cup against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]], Kamada started the match and played 75 minutes before being substituted, as the match eventually ended 1–1 with Japan crashing out after their defeat on penalties.<ref>{{cite news|title=【Match Report】SAMURAI BLUE、クロアチアにPK戦で敗れて16強越えならず|url=http://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/worldcup_2022/news/00031190/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=6 December 2022|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> Reflecting on playing in the World Cup, he expressed his disappointment of being the only starter in the attacking position to not score or provide assists.<ref>{{cite news|title=Lazio, Kamada: "Sono un introverso, preferisco parlare con i fatti"|url=https://www.tuttomercatoweb.com/serie-a/lazio-kamada-sono-un-introverso-preferisco-parlare-con-i-fatti-1874209|website=Tutto Mercato Web|language=it|date=9 September 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref>

Following the World Cup, Kamada received a call–up from Japan for the [[Kirin Cup Soccer#2023 Kirin Challenge Cup|Kirin Challenge Cup]] on 15 March 2023.<ref>{{cite news |date=15 March 2023 |title=日本代表、キリンチャレンジ杯に臨むメンバー26名を発表！ 吉田や長友らは選外に |trans-title=The Japan national team announces the 26 players for the Kirin Challenge Cup! Yoshida, Nagatomo, and others are excluded from the list. |url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/national/20230315/1748013.html |access-date=7 September 2024 |website=Soccer King |language=ja}}</ref> He played his first match for the Samurai Blue since the World Cup, in a 1–1 draw against [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] on 24 March 2023.<ref>{{cite news|title=【Match Report】SAMURAI BLUE、西村選手の同点ゴールでウルグアイ代表とドロー|url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/20230324/news/00031848/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=24 March 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> On 16 November 2023, Kamada scored Japan's second goal of the game, in a 5–0 win against Myanmar.<ref name="Kamada Myanmar 2">{{cite news|title=【Match Report】SAMURAI BLUE、上田選手が3得点などアジア予選初戦でミャンマー代表に快勝|url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/news/00033256/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=16 November 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> However, on 1 January 2024, he was cut from the Japan's squad for the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup|AFC Asian Cup]] in Qatar.<ref>{{cite news|title=SAMURAI BLUE（日本代表）メンバー・スケジュール AFCアジアカップカタール2023（2024.1.12～2.10）|url=https://www.jfa.jp/samuraiblue/news/00033539/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=1 January 2024|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=【日本代表】田中碧、鎌田大地、古橋亨梧らアジア杯メンバーから選外「置かれている状況の中で」|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/202401010000645.html|website=Nikkan Sports|language=ja|date=1 January 2024|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> Kamada was able to make his return to the Samurai Blue squad when he was called up on 24 May 2024.<ref>{{cite news|title=SAMURAI BLUE、6月の2次予選2連戦へ鎌田選手、冨安選手、鈴木唯人選手らが復帰|url=https://www.jfa.jp/news/00033971/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=25 May 2024|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref> Kamada made his first appearance for Japan in six months against Myanmar on 6 June 2024 and set up one of the goals, in a 5–0 win.<ref>{{cite news|title=【Match Report】SAMURAI BLUE 中村選手、小川選手、堂安選手らのゴールでミャンマーに勝利|url=https://www.jfa.jp/news/00034012/|website=Japan Football Association|language=ja|date=6 June 2024|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Kamada's father, Fukushige, was once a footballer and worked for the seniors and juniors at Osaka University of Physical Education.<ref name="Kamada Interview 2">{{cite news |date=22 April 2020 |title=鎌田大地は「やっぱり掴めない」。東山高時代の覚醒と葛藤、そして今 (1) |trans-title=Daichi Kamada is "still elusive." His awakening and struggles during his time at Higashiyama High, and where he is now (1). |url=https://number.bunshun.jp/articles/-/843267?page=1 |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Number Bunshun |language=ja}}</ref> Because of his father's guidance, Kamada worked hard and learned how to use his body, enabling him to go back and forth between the attacking third and middle thirds, and his number of pass variations increased.<ref name="Kamada Interview 3">{{cite news|title=鎌田大地は「やっぱり掴めない」。東山高時代の覚醒と葛藤、そして今 (2)|url=https://number.bunshun.jp/articles/-/843267?page=2|publisher=Number Bunshun|language=ja|date=22 April 2020|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=14 March 2019 |title=鎌田大地の得点力に恩師が太鼓判「振りが全然違う」 |trans-title=Daichi Kamada's scoring ability praised by his mentor: "His technique is completely different." |url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/201903140000648.html |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Nikkan Sports |language=ja}}</ref> He has a younger brother, [[Hiromu Kamada]], who is also a footballer.<ref>{{cite news|title=「兄に少しでも追いつけるように…」 鎌田大地の弟・大夢、福島加入が決定|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/japan/jl/20191223/1012182.html|publisher=Soccer King|language=ja|date=23 December 2019|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> In his free time, Kamada has said he is learning German and reads manga.<ref name="Kamada Interview 6">{{cite news |date=2 April 2020 |title=Eintracht Frankfurt: Daichi Kamada vertreibt sich die Zeit in der Corona-Pause |trans-title=Eintracht Frankfurt: Daichi Kamada passes the time during the Corona break. |url=https://www.fr.de/eintracht-frankfurt/eintracht-frankfurt-kamada-vertreibt-sich-zeit-corona-pause-zr-13638358.html |access-date=19 July 2020 |publisher=Frankfurter Rundschau |language=de}}</ref> Kamada credited teammate [[Makoto Hasebe]] for helping him settle down in Germany.<ref>{{cite news|title=「自分はあまりいいドリブラーとは思わない」。鎌田大地が語る自身の特徴、譲れないポイント|url=https://www.goal.com/jp/%E3%83%8B%E3%83%A5%E3%83%BC%E3%82%B9/bundesliga-eintracht-frankfurt-daichi-kamada-20201208/97c5f48jo66u192de8ful6fzk|website=Goal.com|language=ja|date=9 December 2020|access-date=7 September 2024}}<br>{{cite news|title=鎌田大地が同僚の長谷部誠についてコメント「友人というより兄のよう」|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/world/ger/20210513/1398014.html|website=Soccer King|language=ja|date=13 May 2021|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref>

At one point, Kamada considered going to university, saying: "Going to college may be a necessary path for me, but I still have a feeling that I can't give up. If I become a professional after graduating from college, I'm already 22 years old. However, I thought it would be very late to become a professional at the age of 22. For me, it is ideal that I go to the J League from high school and start from the first year, and I think I should do that. And I'm thinking about the future of the J League. I've always had a dream to go out into the world and play. I don't appreciate it, but I have enough confidence to do it."<ref>{{cite news|title=鎌田大地は「やっぱり掴めない」。東山高時代の覚醒と葛藤、そして今 (3)|url=https://number.bunshun.jp/articles/-/843267?page=3|publisher=Number Bunshun|language=ja|date=22 April 2020|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> Growing up, Kamada said he wanted to be a footballer.<ref>{{cite news|title=「自分が成長するには一番の場所」東山FW鎌田が鳥栖入団会見|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?151811-151811-fl|publisher=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=18 November 2014|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> On 25 May 2017, Kamada announced his marriage, to a woman he had been dating for a long time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sagan-tosu.net/news/p/2151/|title=鎌田大地選手 入籍のお知らせ|website=Sagan Tosu|language=ja|date=25 May 2017|access-date=7 September 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20240414073713/https://www.sagan-tosu.net/news/p/2151/|archive-date=14 April 2024|url-status=live}}</ref> A year later in October 2018, he became a first time father when his wife gave birth to a baby boy.<ref>{{cite news|title=鎌田大地が第1子誕生を祝う今季3ゴール目！ 勝利に貢献しチームは6試合負けなし|url=https://www.soccer-king.jp/news/world/world_other/20181007/843599.html|publisher=Soccer King|language=ja|date=7 October 2018|access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref> Since moving to Eintracht Frankfurt, Kamada resides in the city with his family.<ref name="Kamada Interview 6"/>

In July 2023, Kamada released his first book titled ''Unwavering Conviction: 12 People Testify: Japan National Team Soccer Player Kamada Daichi's Growth Story''.<ref>{{cite news|title=日本代表MF鎌田大地の公式バイオグラフィーが7月5日に発売|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/book/detail/?387580-387580-fl|website=Web Gekisaka|language=ja|date=5 July 2023|access-date=7 September 2024}}</ref>

